description: Eswatini ""is enforcing a health monitoring on all persons who had contact with positive tested persons, at hospital entrance points, Clients calling the emergency toll-free line reporting symptoms of COVID-19, returned travelers and police road blocks for the next three weeks after April 15"".
Eswatini is enforcing health monitoring to all patients that have been confirmed positive after April 21.
In Eswatini, ""employers are expected to provide facilities for employees to wash their hands"" after March 27.

Eswatini ""Government has established a COVID-19 testing Laboratory in Mbabane and is working to upgrade the Lubombo Referral Laboratory for COVID-19 testing. In the next weeks the goverment will train additional staff members on COVID-19 testing to increase capacity at the Mbabane Molecular Laboratory after March 15""

Eswatini increases health resources by ""building capacity to be able to safely treat all patients requiring hospitalization"" after April. 15. (additional beds, ventilators and recruited additional staff)
Eswatini is ""renovating some of the health facilities to increase isolation capacity of the country"", announced April.15.
Many public spaces and communities in Eswatini have been assisted with hand washing facilities, including 506 water tanks, which is announced April.15.
Eswatini ""is increasing the numbers of scanners after April 22""

Eswatini ""ensures availability of face masks to minimize the spread of the virus after April 22""

Eswatini ""is enforcing a health testing on all people who had contact with already positive tested persons, at the entrance points of hospitals, all returned travelers, all clients who called the emergency toll free line for reporting symptoms of Covid-19 for the next three weeks after April 15"".
Eswatini ""is enforcing a health testing on all their frontline healthcare workers after April 15"".
The process of disinfecting public spaces has been initiated mainly in Eswatini's cities and it will soon be extended to Eswatini's towns announced April. 15.
Eswatini ""is encouraging the citizens to minimize non essential local travel after March 17""
In Eswatini, ""non-essential travel"" within country ""is not permitted, except for medical reasons or to provide or acquire essential services"" after March 27.
